    dc:creator "Casale, Achille; Shi, Hongliang" ;
    dc:date "2018" ;
    dc:title "Revision of the Oriental species of Calleida Latreille (sensu lato). Part 1: Introduction, groups of species, and species of six species groups (Coleoptera: Carabidae: Lebiini)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1302717>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1302725>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1302733>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1302735>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1302721>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1302741>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1302737>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1302727> .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1302717>
    dc:description "FIGURES 19–21. Calleida gressittiana sp. n. 19 habitus and labels of holotype (male, Kinabalu, Borneo, MNHN), scale bar = 2.0 mm; 20 habitus of paratype (female, Sandakan, Borneo, NHML), scale bar = 2.0 mm; 21 median lobe of aedeagus, rightlateral, ventral, left-lateral, and dorsal views (holotype), scale bar = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1302717/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1302725>
    dc:description "FIGURES 30–35. Calleida lativittis Chaudoir. 30 habitus and labels of lectotype (female, \"Deccan\", MNHN), scale bar = 2.0 mm; 31 habitus of paralectotype (female, \"Deccan\", MNHN), scale bar = 2.0 mm; 32–35 male genitalia, scale bar = 0.5 mm: 32 median lobe of aedeagus, dorsal view; 33 left paramere of aedeagus; 34 median lobe of aedeagus, left-lateral view; 35 male sternum IX." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1302725/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1302733>
    dc:description "FIGURES 44–47. Calleida terminata Waterhouse. 44 habitus and labels of lectotype (male, Sarawak, Malaysia, NHML), scale bar = 2.0 mm; 45 median lobe of aedeagus, right-lateral, ventral, left-lateral, and dorsal views (lectotype), scale bar = 0.5 mm; 46 left and right parameres of aedeagus (lectotype), scale bar = 0.2 mm; 47 male sternum IX (lectotype), scale bar = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1302733/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1302735>
    dc:description "FIGURES 48–55. Calleida corporaali Andrewes. 48 habitus (female, Sabah, Malaysia), scale bar = 2.0 mm; 49 habitus and labels of lectotype for C. corporaali Andrewes (male, Sumatra, NHML), scale bar = 2.0 mm; 50 habitus and labels of lectotype for C. lieftincki Louwerens (female, Borneo, NNML), scale bar = 2.0 mm; 51 median lobe of aedeagus, right-lateral, ventral, left-lateral, and dorsal views (lectotype), scale bar = 0.5 mm; 52 left and right parameres of aedeagus (lectotype), scale bar = 0.2 mm; 53 male sternum IX (lectotype), scale bar = 0.5 mm; 54 ovipositor (Sabah, Malaysia), scale bar = 0.2 mm; 55 female reproductive tract (Sabah, Malaysia), scale bar = 0.5 mm; abbreviations: sp spermatheca, pd spermathecal pedicel, gd spermathecal gland duct, ga glandular area, at atrium, bpl basal sclerotized plate." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1302735/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1302721>
    dc:description "FIGURES 22–29. Calleida puncticollis sp. n. 22 habitus and labels of holotype (male, Hubei, IZAS), scale bar = 2.0 mm; 23 habitus of paratype (female, Shaanxi, IZAS), scale bar = 2.0 mm; 24 pronotum (Shaanxi, China), [coarsely punctate], scale bar = 0.5 mm; 25 ovipositor (Hubei, China), scale bar = 0.1 mm; 26 female reproductive tract (Hubei, China), scale bar = 0.5 mm; 27 median lobe of aedeagus, right-lateral, ventral, left-lateral, and dorsal views (holotype), scale bar = 0.5 mm; 28 left and right parameres of aedeagus (holotype), scale bar = 0.2 mm; 29 male sternum IX (holotype), scale bar = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1302721/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1302741>
    dc:description "FIGURES 61–66. Calleida borneensis sp. n. 61 habitus and labels of holotype (male, Sabah, Malaysia, NHML), scale bar = 2.0 mm; 62 habitus of paratype (male, Sarawak, Malaysia, NHML), scale bar = 2.0 mm; 63 female reproductive tract (Sabah, Malaysia), scale bar = 0.5 mm; abbreviations: sp spermatheca, pd spermathecal pedicel, gd spermathecal gland duct, ga glandular area, at atrium, bpj spermathecal basal projection, apt pedicel apical protuberance; 64 median lobe of aedeagus, right-lateral, ventral, left-lateral, and dorsal views (holotype), scale bar = 0.5 mm; 65 left and right parameres of aedeagus (holotype), scale bar = 0.2 mm; 66 ovipositor (Sabah, Malaysia), scale bar = 0.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1302741/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1302737>
    dc:description "FIGURES 56–60. Calleida viet sp. n. 56 habitus and labels of holotype (male, Vung Tau, Vietnam, CCA), scale bar = 2.0 mm; 57–59 male genitalia (holotype), scale bar = 0.5 mm: 57 median lobe of aedeagus, ventral view; 58 left paramere of aedeagus; 59 median lobe of aedeagus, left-lateral view; 60 female reproductive tract and ovipositor (paratype), scale bar = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1302737/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1302727>
    dc:description "FIGURES 36–41. Calleida excelsa Bates. 36 habitus and labels of lectotype (female, Carin Chebà, Myanmar, MSNG), scale bar = 2.0 mm; 37 habitus of paralectotype (female, Senmigion, Myanmar, MNHN), scale bar = 2.0 mm; 38 habitus (female, Yunnan, China), scale bar = 2.0 mm; 39 female reproductive tract (Chiang Mai, Thailand), scale bar = 0.5 mm; 40 ovipositor (Yunnan, China), scale bar = 0.2 mm; 41 apex of immature aedeagus, left-lateral view, scale bar = 0.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1302727/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

